cates. smtplib uses default certificate verification which may not catch MITM attacks depending on Python version and platform. Consider using proper certificate validation.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"medium\",\n      \"file\": \"notify.py\",\n      \"line\": 72,\n      \"description\": \"SMTP credentials accessed via os.environ without existence check. Accessing os.environ['SMTP_USER'] and os.environ['SMTP_PASS'] directly will raise KeyError if not set, despite the existence check for SMTP_USER. Also, credentials are passed in plaintext over SMTP_HOST.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"file\": \"notify.py\",\n      \"line\": 46,\n      \"description\": \"Missing error handling for Slack webhook POST request. Error responses are silently ignored, making debugging notification failures difficult and potentially hiding account compromise.\",\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"file\": \"notify.py\",\n      \"line\": 55,\n      \"description\": \"Missing error handling for generic webhook POST request. Error responses are silently ignored. HTTP errors could indicate webhook misconfiguration or endpoint being compromised.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"file\": \"fetchers.py\",\n      \"line\": 205,\n      \"description\": \"Regex pattern with unbounded quantifiers (.*?) could potentially be vulnerable to ReDoS attacks if Google's career page HTML structure changes unexpectedly. Specially crafted input could cause excessive backtracking.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"file\": \"fetchers.py\",\n      \"line\": 271,\n      \"description\": \"HTML content from career pages is unescaped (html.unescape) but job titles containing special characters could still cause issues in downstream consumers expecting plain text. Consider validating/sanitizing after unescaping.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"file\": \"pipeline.py\",\n      \"line\": 15,\n      \"description\": \"No schema validation for loaded YAML config. Missing required fields (sources, db, etc.) will silently use defaults rather than failing fast, making misconfigurations harder to catch.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"riskScore\": 62,\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"Add URL validation and allowlist for WEBHOOK_URL and SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL environment variables. Restrict to HTTPS only and known domains.\",\n    \"Implement strict certificate verification for SMTP connections using ssl.create_default_context()\",\n    \"Disable HTTP redirect following or implement safe redirect validation that only allows redirects within the same domain\",\n    \"Fix SMTP credential access: Use os.getenv() with defaults or check existence before accessing os.environ\",\n    \"Add proper error handling and logging for all webhook POST requests to surface failures in CI/CD logs\",\n    \"Implement input validation for mode_words in agent.py to ensure no shell metacharacters can be passed through\",\n    \"Add schema validation for sources.yaml configuration using a library like pydantic or cerberus to fail fast on invalid configs\",\n    \"Consider using a more robust regex or HTML parser (like BeautifulSoup) instead of regex patterns for parsing career page HTML to avoid ReDoS vulnerabilities\",\n    \"Add URL validation helper that checks scheme is https:// before making external HTTP requests from config\",\n    \"Implement rate limiting and timeout enforcement to prevent abuse of the scraper by malicious job board endpoints\",\n    \"Document which environment variables must be set and add validation in __main__ to check them before execution\",\n    \"For Slack messages, ensure all user-controlled content (job titles, company names) is properly escaped to prevent message injection\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Summary\n\n**Overall Risk Score: 62/100 (Medium-High)**\n\n### Key Findings:\n\n1. **SSRF Vulnerabilities (Critical Control)**: The biggest risk is SSRF attacks via webhook URLs and HTTP re